              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33776f9n/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>Now I, by no means, intend to advise, a mean, time<lb/> serving policy: being all\n                things unto all men<lb/> we should have fixed <hi rend=\"underline\">principles</hi>,\n                and should adhere to<lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">them</hi> at every <sic>hazzard</sic>. But there are many\n                things<lb/> in which <hi rend=\"underline\">principle</hi> is not involved, and then\n                it is<lb/> not only our right but it is our duty (if we desire<lb/> success) to use\n                the <hi rend=\"underline\">suaviter<add>?</add> in modo</hi> to flatter<lb/> (not at\n                the expense of principle) the petty vanities of<lb/> those among whom we live and to\n                bend these very<lb/> follies to our own use. If a man wants to be servic-<lb/>able\n                in his calling—be it what it may—he<lb/> must command the love and respect of\n                those<lb/> among whom his lot is cast; and to do this<lb/> he must be firm—honest\n                &amp; honorable—and he<lb/> must also yield to their wishes in <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >minor</hi> things.<lb/> But excuse me. I may perhaps tire you, but at<lb/> any\n                rate be assured that all that I do say<lb/> is prompted by a sincere friendship and\n                a<lb/> desire for your welfare &amp; happiness.</p>\n            <p>I would beg you to be <hi rend=\"underline\">sure</hi> of success before<lb/> you\n                undertake any of the new works you now<lb/> propose. Continue if possible the\n                Occident.<lb/> Send it hereafter to <persName>Mr. D. L. Cohen</persName>,\n                    <placeName>Savannah Geo.</placeName><lb/> who you may put down as a permanent,\n                paying<lb/> subscriber. My family join in kindest regards.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(8)\">Yrs most truly</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(9)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Solomon Cohen</persName>\n            </p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33776f9n/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
